  <summary>Two policemen must join forces to take on an international drug- smuggling gang - one, an unorthodox Irish policeman and the other, a straitlaced FBI agent. Sergeant Gerry Boyle is an eccentric small-town cop with a confrontational and crass personality and a subversive sense of humor. A longtime policeman in County Galway, Boyle is a maverick with his own moral code. He has seen enough of the world to know there isn't much to it and has had plenty of time to think about it. When a fellow police officer disappears and Boyle's small town becomes key to a large drug trafficking investigation, he is forced to at least feign interest when dealing with the humorless FBI agent Wendell Everett assigned to the case.</summary>
  <reviews>
    <item index="0">
      <text>Although The Guard is primarily a language romp, it's also a terrific showcase for veteran pug-faced character actor Brendan Gleeson.</text>
      <source>Globe and Mail</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/arts/movies/the-guard-bloody-funny-drug-busting-buddies/article2141865/</link>
      <author>Liam Lacey</author>
    </item>
    <item index="1">
      <text>Crisp, acid-tongued and sharply acted, it's the sort of exercise in tangy Celtic cynicism that's become one of the Emerald Isle's most reliable imports.</text>
      <source>Houston Chronicle</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://events.29-95.com/reviews/show/14030605-review-the-guard</link>
      <author>Amy Biancolli</author>
    </item>
    <item index="2">
      <text>There are few things finer in cinema than Brendan Gleeson's fat, happy face.</text>
      <source>Detroit News</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://detroitnews.com/article/20110819/ENT02/108190317/1034/ent02/Brendan-Gleeson-shines-alongside-Don-Cheadle-in-%E2%80%98The-Guard%E2%80%99</link>
      <author>Tom Long</author>
    </item>
    <item index="3">
      <text>McDonagh's script is agile, darting between the ridiculous, the sage and the surprisingly sentimental. His love of language and the absurd has hints of the wisecracking Quentin Tarantino. But the story is decidedly more rooted in Ireland's loamy turf.</text>
      <source>Denver Post</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.denverpost.com/movies</link>
      <author>Lisa Kennedy</author>
    </item>
    <item index="4">
      <text>"The Guard" is violent, profane and funny.</text>
      <source>St. Louis Post-Dispatch</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/movies/reviews/article_c1e0561c-a277-5b99-b088-b7659a7e9478.html</link>
      <author>Joe Williams</author>
    </item>
    <item index="5">
      <text>"The Guard" is not the most original buddy-cop movie you'll see, but it well may be one of the most entertaining.</text>
      <source>Arizona Republic</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.azcentral.com/thingstodo/movies/articles/2011/08/17/20110817guard-movie-review-goodykoontz.html</link>
      <author>Bill Goodykoontz</author>
    </item>
    <item index="6">
      <text>A hugely entertaining but frustratingly disorganised film, packed with priceless moments which never quite coalesce into a rewarding whole.</text>
      <source>Time Out</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.timeout.com/film/reviews/90161/the-guard.html</link>
      <author>Tom Huddleston</author>
    </item>
    <item index="7">
      <text>"The Guard" himself may be no angel, but his movie is a wee slice of heaven.</text>
      <source>Washington Post</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.washingtonpost.com/gog/movies/the-guard,1178474/critic-review.html</link>
      <author>Ann Hornaday</author>
    </item>
    <item index="8">
      <text>Like an Irish version of "In the Heat of the Night," the profane and frequently hilarious "The Guard" watches the sparks fly as a smart African-American detective teams up with an unapologetically racist County Galway policeman.</text>
      <source>Seattle Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://feeds.seattletimes.com/click.phdo?i=f936c8b361519b27cbaeb93ae99db088</link>
      <author>John Hartl</author>
    </item>
    <item index="9">
      <text>Rich with inspired musings on pop culture, literature, philosophy, race, sex.</text>
      <source>Philadelphia Inquirer</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/20110812_Cops_and_comedy_in_a_zesty_Irish_stew.html</link>
      <author>Steven Rea</author>
    </item>
    <item index="10">
      <text>This black comedy needed to be a whole lot blacker and funnier.</text>
      <source>Christian Science Monitor</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.csmonitor.com/The-Culture/Movies/2011/0729/The-Guard-movie-review</link>
      <author>Peter Rainer</author>
    </item>
    <item index="11">
      <text>Brendan Gleeson, as beefily Irish an actor as anyone since Victor McLaglen, is always believable and frequently hilarious.</text>
      <source>Chicago Reader</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.chicagoreader.com/chicago/MovieTimes?oid=4358349</link>
      <author>Michael Wilmington</author>
    </item>
    <item index="12">
      <text>When it's over it evaporates, leaving only the acrid smoke of its dialogue and the memory of Gleeson reducing lesser mortals to cinders.</text>
      <source>Boston Globe</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://feeds.boston.com/click.phdo?i=197fa5ba6e5ce81149b836070c8d18a7</link>
      <author>Ty Burr</author>
    </item>
    <item index="13">
      <text>"The Guard" is a pleasure. I can't tell if it's really (bleeping) dumb or really (bleeping) smart, but it's pretty (bleeping) good.</text>
      <source>Chicago Sun-Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.rogerebert.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20110803/REVIEWS/110809995/-1/RSS</link>
      <author>Roger Ebert</author>
    </item>
    <item index="14">
      <text>If the movie's mix of nihilistic violence and snarky attitude suggests In Bruges, it's a family resemblance.</text>
      <source>NPR</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.npr.org/2011/07/28/138714509/the-guard-corruption-and-violence-with-a-smile</link>
      <author>Mark Jenkins</author>
    </item>
    <item index="15">
      <text>"The Guard," alas, is just as flawed as Gerry. But occasionally - when Gleeson or Cheadle or Flanagan is on screen - it's nice to pretend it isn't.</text>
      <source>Newark Star-Ledger</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.nj.com/entertainment/movies/index.ssf/2011/07/the_guard_movie_review_actors_have_some_great_moments_as_us_and_irish_lawmen_improbably_forced_to_wo.html</link>
      <author>Stephen Whitty</author>
    </item>
    <item index="16">
      <text>McDonagh indulges in too many '90s affectations, from blaring chapter titles to philosophizing gangsters. But he captures his misty setting's insular atmosphere beautifully.</text>
      <source>New York Daily News</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/2011/07/29/2011-07-29_short_takes_the_guard_the_future_attack_the_block.html?r=entertainment/movies</link>
      <author>Elizabeth Weitzman</author>
    </item>
    <item index="17">
      <text>McDonagh is your man when it comes to cruelly funny dialogue, and Gleeson makes it sing and sting.</text>
      <source>New York Post</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/movies/ace_script_in_wild_guard_L11bZcSj4OSDu30fsDBLkN?CMP=OTC-rss&amp;FEEDNAME=</link>
      <author>Kyle Smith</author>
    </item>
  </reviews>
